body_html:
Hi,

Consumer ops are not the same as t.op. Simply speaking, t.op is the op producing the tensor and consumer ops are the ops taking t as input.

So I think this is working as expected (correct me if I am wrong!).

body:
Hi,

Consumer ops are not the same as t.op. Simply speaking, `t.op` is the op producing the tensor and consumer ops are the ops taking `t` as input.

So I think this is working as expected (correct me if I am wrong!).
